              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-33531" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Physics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Physics              : An elementary course on astronomy and astrophysics. Positional astronomy and finding your way about the sky. Our evolving picture of the universe. Properties and origins of the solar system. The Big Bang and modern cosmology.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        David Hanna (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students in a Physics program. Not open to students who have taken PHYS 204 or PHYS 205.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
