                <h4>Social Studies</h4>

    
              <p>Students may take up to 12 credits from this list below which represents a balance of History (HIST), Geography (GEOG), and Citizenship courses offered by several departments. Anthropology (ANTH) and Sociology (SOCI) courses not on the list below may not be counted as Social Studies courses in the program requirements. Students may take them as electives only.</p>
<p>Students may select additional History courses as follows:<br />
Any 3 credits in European History<br />
Any 3 credits in Asian, African, or Latin American History<br />
Any 3 credits in any topic or field of history</p>
<p>* Note: Courses marked with an asterisk ("*") may be used as Ethics and Religious Culture or Social Studies courses.</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/anth-202" class="program-course-title">
